<h1>ğŸ©º Medical Insurance Cost Prediction</h1>

<p>This project builds a predictive model to estimate individual medical insurance charges based on demographic and lifestyle attributes using Linear Regression. It also includes data-driven insights and business recommendations.</p>

<h2>ğŸ“Œ Objective</h2>
<ul>
<li>Analyze key drivers of medical insurance costs</li>
<li>Build a regression model to predict charges</li>
<li>Provide actionable insights for insurance pricing strategy</li>
</ul>

<h2>ğŸ§© Dataset Overview</h2>
<p>Sourced from Kaggle: <a href="https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/mirichoi0218/insurance">Medical Cost Personal Dataset</a></p>

<table>
<tr><th>Feature</th><th>Description</th></tr>
<tr><td>age</td><td>Age of insured individual</td></tr>
<tr><td>sex</td><td>Gender of policyholder</td></tr>
<tr><td>bmi</td><td>Body Mass Index</td></tr>
<tr><td>children</td><td>Number of dependents</td></tr>
<tr><td>smoker</td><td>Smoking status</td></tr>
<tr><td>region</td><td>Residential region in the US</td></tr>
<tr><td>charges</td><td>Billed medical charges</td></tr>
</table>

<h2>ğŸ” Exploratory Analysis</h2>
<ul>
<li>Distribution charts for age, charges, children, BMI</li>
<li>Pie charts for categorical features (sex, smoker, region)</li>
<li>BMI categorized into health levels</li>
<li>3D bar plot for average cost by age group and smoking status</li>
</ul>

<h2>âš™ï¸ Data Preparation</h2>
<ul>
<li>Outlier removal using Z-score</li>
<li>One-hot encoding for categorical features</li>
<li>Feature scaling with StandardScaler</li>
<li>Engineered feature: <code>age * charges</code> for interaction</li>
</ul>

<h2>ğŸ¤– Modeling â€“ Linear Regression</h2>
<ul>
<li><strong>RÂ² Score</strong>: 0.92</li>
<li><strong>RMSE</strong>: 0.28</li>
<li>The model performs well without overfitting</li>
</ul>

<h3>ğŸ” Feature Importance</h3>
<ul>
<li>Smoking status is the top cost driver</li>
<li>Obesity and number of children are secondary drivers</li>
<li>Age and region also influence cost moderately</li>
</ul>

<h2>ğŸ’¡ Business Insights</h2>
<ul>
<li>Target high-risk groups (smokers, obese individuals)</li>
<li>Use pricing tiers for risk-based premiums</li>
<li>Launch preventive programs to reduce future payouts</li>
</ul>

